{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"The career that I started early on in my life"},{"time":3000,"text":"was looking for exotic life forms in exotic places,"},{"time":7000,"text":"and at that time I was working in the Antarctic and the Arctic,"},{"time":10000,"text":"and high deserts and low deserts."},{"time":12000,"text":"Until about a dozen years ago, when I was really captured by caves,"},{"time":15000,"text":"and I really re-focused most of my research in that direction."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19000,"text":"So I have a really cool day job-- I get to do some really amazing stuff."},{"time":22000,"text":"I work in some of the most extreme cave environments on the planet."},{"time":26000,"text":"Many of them are trying to kill us from the minute we go into them,"},{"time":28000,"text":"but nevertheless, they're absolutely gripping,"},{"time":31000,"text":"and contain unbelievable biological wonders"},{"time":33000,"text":"that are very, very different from those that we have on the planet."},{"time":36000,"text":"Apart from the intrinsic value"},{"time":38000,"text":"of the biology and mineralogy and geo-microbiology that we do there,"},{"time":41000,"text":"we're also using these as templates"},{"time":43000,"text":"for figuring out how to go look"},{"time":45000,"text":"for life on other planets."},{"time":47000,"text":"Particularly Mars, but also Europa,"},{"time":49000,"text":"the small, icy moon around Jupiter."},{"time":52000,"text":"And perhaps, someday, far beyond our solar system itself."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55000,"text":"I'm very passionately interested in the human future,"},{"time":58000,"text":"on the Moon and Mars particularly,"},{"time":60000,"text":"and elsewhere in the solar system."},{"time":62000,"text":"I think it's time that we transitioned"},{"time":64000,"text":"to a solar system-going civilization and species."},{"time":67000,"text":"And, as an outgrowth of all of this then,"},{"time":70000,"text":"I wonder about whether we can, and whether we even should,"},{"time":73000,"text":"think about transporting Earth-type life to other planets."},{"time":77000,"text":"Notably Mars, as a first example."}]},{"cues":[{"time":79000,"text":"Something I never talk about in scientific meetings"},{"time":81000,"text":"is how I actually got to this state"},{"time":83000,"text":"and why I do the work that I do."},{"time":85000,"text":"Why don't I have a normal job, a sensible job?"},{"time":88000,"text":"And then of course, I blame the Soviet Union."},{"time":91000,"text":"Because in the mid-1950s,"},{"time":93000,"text":"when I was a tiny child,"},{"time":95000,"text":"they had the audacity to launch"},{"time":97000,"text":"a very primitive little satellite called Sputnik,"},{"time":100000,"text":"which sent the Western world into a hysterical tailspin."},{"time":104000,"text":"And a tremendous amount of money"},{"time":106000,"text":"went into the funding of science"},{"time":108000,"text":"and mathematics skills for kids."},{"time":110000,"text":"And I'm a product of that generation,"},{"time":112000,"text":"like so many other of my peers."},{"time":114000,"text":"It really caught hold of us, and caught fire,"},{"time":116000,"text":"and it would be lovely if we could reproduce that again now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":119000,"text":"Of course, refusing to grow up --"},{"time":121000,"text":"-- even though I impersonate a grown-up in daily life,"},{"time":124000,"text":"but I do a fairly good job of that --"},{"time":126000,"text":"but really retaining that childlike quality"},{"time":128000,"text":"of not caring what other people think"},{"time":130000,"text":"about what you're interested in, is really critical."},{"time":133000,"text":"The next element is the fact that"},{"time":135000,"text":"I have applied a value judgment"},{"time":137000,"text":"and my value judgment is that the presence of life"},{"time":139000,"text":"is better than no life."},{"time":141000,"text":"And so, life is more valuable than no life."},{"time":143000,"text":"And so I think that that holds together"},{"time":146000,"text":"a great deal of the work"},{"time":148000,"text":"that people in this audience approach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152000,"text":"I'm very interested in Mars, of course,"},{"time":155000,"text":"and that was a product of my being a young undergraduate"},{"time":159000,"text":"when the Viking Landers landed on Mars."},{"time":162000,"text":"And that took what had been"},{"time":164000,"text":"a tiny little astronomical object in the sky,"},{"time":167000,"text":"that you would see as a dot,"},{"time":169000,"text":"and turned it completely into a landscape,"},{"time":173000,"text":"as that very first primitive picture"},{"time":175000,"text":"came rastering across the screen."},{"time":177000,"text":"And when it became a landscape,"},{"time":179000,"text":"it also became a destination,"},{"time":181000,"text":"and altered, really, the course of my life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":185000,"text":"In my graduate years I worked with"},{"time":187000,"text":"my colleague and mentor and friend, Steve Schneider,"},{"time":189000,"text":"at the National Center for Atmospheric Research,"},{"time":191000,"text":"working on global change issues."},{"time":194000,"text":"We've written a number of things on"},{"time":196000,"text":"the role of Gaia hypothesis --"},{"time":197000,"text":"whether or not you could consider Earth as a single entity"},{"time":200000,"text":"in any meaningful scientific sense,"},{"time":202000,"text":"and then, as an outgrowth of that,"},{"time":204000,"text":"I worked on the environmental consequences of nuclear war."}]},{"cues":[{"time":208000,"text":"So, wonderful things and grim things."},{"time":210000,"text":"But what it taught me was to look at Earth as a planet"},{"time":213000,"text":"with external eyes, not just as our home."},{"time":216000,"text":"And that is a wonderful stepping away in perspective,"},{"time":220000,"text":"to try to then think about the way"},{"time":222000,"text":"our planet behaves, as a planet,"},{"time":225000,"text":"and with the life that's on it."},{"time":227000,"text":"And all of this seems to me to be"},{"time":230000,"text":"a salient point in history."},{"time":232000,"text":"We're getting ready to begin to go"},{"time":234000,"text":"through the process of leaving our planet of origin"},{"time":237000,"text":"and out into the wider solar system and beyond."}]},{"cues":[{"time":241000,"text":"So, back to Mars."},{"time":243000,"text":"How hard is it going to be to find life on Mars?"},{"time":245000,"text":"Well, sometimes it's really very hard for us to find each other,"},{"time":247000,"text":"even on this planet."},{"time":249000,"text":"So, finding life on another planet"},{"time":251000,"text":"is a non-trivial occupation"},{"time":253000,"text":"and we spend a lot of time trying to think about that."},{"time":256000,"text":"Whether or not you think it's likely to be successful"},{"time":258000,"text":"sort of depends on what you think about"},{"time":260000,"text":"the chances of life in the universe."},{"time":262000,"text":"I think, myself,"},{"time":264000,"text":"that life is a natural outgrowth"},{"time":267000,"text":"of the increasing complexification of matter over time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270000,"text":"So, you start with the Big Bang and you get hydrogen,"},{"time":272000,"text":"and then you get helium, and then you get more complicated stuff,"},{"time":274000,"text":"and you get planets forming --"},{"time":276000,"text":"and life is a common, planetary-based phenomenon, in my view."},{"time":280000,"text":"Certainly, in the last 15 years,"},{"time":282000,"text":"we've seen increasing numbers of planets"},{"time":285000,"text":"outside of our solar system being confirmed,"},{"time":288000,"text":"and just last month, a couple of weeks ago,"},{"time":291000,"text":"a planet in the size-class of Earth"},{"time":293000,"text":"has actually been found."},{"time":295000,"text":"And so this is very exciting news."}]},{"cues":[{"time":297000,"text":"So, my first bold prediction is that,"},{"time":299000,"text":"is that in the universe, life is going to be everywhere."},{"time":302000,"text":"It's going to be everywhere we look --"},{"time":304000,"text":"where there are planetary systems that can possibly support it."},{"time":307000,"text":"And those planetary systems are going to be very common."},{"time":310000,"text":"So, what about life on Mars?"},{"time":312000,"text":"Well, if somebody had asked me about a dozen years ago"},{"time":314000,"text":"what I thought the chances of life on Mars would be,"},{"time":317000,"text":"I would've probably said, a couple of percent."},{"time":320000,"text":"And even that was considered outrageous at the time."},{"time":323000,"text":"I was once sneeringly introduced"},{"time":325000,"text":"by a former NASA official,"},{"time":327000,"text":"as the only person on the planet"},{"time":329000,"text":"who still thought there was life on Mars."},{"time":331000,"text":"Of course, that official is now dead, and I'm not,"},{"time":333000,"text":"so there's a certain amount of glory"},{"time":336000,"text":"in outliving your adversaries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":338000,"text":"But things have changed greatly"},{"time":340000,"text":"over the last dozen years."},{"time":343000,"text":"And the reason that they have changed"},{"time":345000,"text":"is because we now have new information."},{"time":347000,"text":"The amazing Pathfinder mission that went in '97,"},{"time":350000,"text":"and the MER Rover missions"},{"time":352000,"text":"that are on Mars as we speak now"},{"time":354000,"text":"and the European Space Agency's Mars Express,"},{"time":357000,"text":"has taught us a number of amazing things."},{"time":359000,"text":"There is sub-surface ice on that planet."},{"time":362000,"text":"And so where there is water,"},{"time":364000,"text":"there is a very high chance of our kind of life."},{"time":366000,"text":"There's clearly sedimentary rocks all over the place –"},{"time":368000,"text":"one of the landers is sitting in the middle of an ancient seabed,"},{"time":371000,"text":"and there are these amazing structures called blueberries,"},{"time":375000,"text":"which are these little, rocky concretions"},{"time":377000,"text":"that we are busy making biologically"},{"time":379000,"text":"in my lab right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":381000,"text":"So, with all of these things put together,"},{"time":383000,"text":"I think that the chances of life"},{"time":385000,"text":"are much greater than I would've ever thought."},{"time":387000,"text":"I think that the chance of life having arisen on Mars, sometime in its past,"},{"time":391000,"text":"is maybe one in four to maybe even half and half."},{"time":394000,"text":"So this is a very bold statement."},{"time":396000,"text":"I think it's there, and I think we need"},{"time":398000,"text":"to go look for it, and I think it's underground."},{"time":400000,"text":"So the game's afoot, and this is the game that we play in astro-biology."},{"time":404000,"text":"How do you try to get a handle on extraterrestrial life?"},{"time":407000,"text":"How do you plan to look for it?"},{"time":409000,"text":"How do you know it when you find it?"},{"time":411000,"text":"Because if it's big and obvious, we would've already found it --"},{"time":413000,"text":"it would've already bitten us on the foot, and it hasn't."}]},{"cues":[{"time":416000,"text":"So, we know that it's probably quite cryptic."},{"time":418000,"text":"Very critically, how do we protect it,"},{"time":420000,"text":"if we find it, and not contaminate it?"},{"time":423000,"text":"And also, even perhaps more critically, because"},{"time":426000,"text":"this is the only home planet we have,"},{"time":428000,"text":"how do we protect us from it, while we study it?"},{"time":432000,"text":"So why might it be hard to find?"},{"time":434000,"text":"Well, it's probably microscopic, and it's never easy"},{"time":436000,"text":"to study microscopic things,"},{"time":438000,"text":"although the amazing tools that we now have to do that"},{"time":441000,"text":"allow us to study things in much greater depth,"},{"time":443000,"text":"at much smaller scales than ever before."},{"time":446000,"text":"But it's probably hiding, because if you are out"},{"time":449000,"text":"sequestering resources from your environment, that makes you yummy,"},{"time":452000,"text":"and other things might want to eat you, or consume you."},{"time":454000,"text":"And so, there's a game of predator-prey"},{"time":457000,"text":"that's going to be, essentially, universal, really,"},{"time":462000,"text":"in any kind of biological system."},{"time":464000,"text":"It also may be very, very different in its fundamental properties –"},{"time":467000,"text":"its chemistry, or its size."}]},{"cues":[{"time":469000,"text":"We say small, but what does that mean?"},{"time":471000,"text":"Is it virus-sized? Is it smaller than that?"},{"time":473000,"text":"Is it bigger than the biggest bacterium? We don't know."},{"time":475000,"text":"And speed of activity, which is something that we face"},{"time":478000,"text":"in our work with sub-surface organisms,"},{"time":480000,"text":"because they grow very, very slowly."},{"time":482000,"text":"If I were to take a swab off your teeth"},{"time":485000,"text":"and plate it on a Petri plate,"},{"time":487000,"text":"within about four or five hours, I would have to see growth."},{"time":490000,"text":"But the organisms that we work with,"},{"time":492000,"text":"from the sub-surface of Earth,"},{"time":493000,"text":"very often it's months -- and in many cases, years --"},{"time":496000,"text":"before we see any growth whatsoever."},{"time":498000,"text":"So they are, intrinsically, a slower life-form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501000,"text":"But the real issue is that we are guided by"},{"time":504000,"text":"our limited experience,"},{"time":506000,"text":"and until we can think out of the box of our cranium and what we know,"},{"time":510000,"text":"then we can't recognize what to look for,"},{"time":512000,"text":"or how to plan for it."},{"time":515000,"text":"So, perspective is everything"},{"time":517000,"text":"and, because of the history that I've just briefly talked to you about,"},{"time":520000,"text":"I have learned to think about Earth"},{"time":522000,"text":"as an extraterrestrial planet."},{"time":524000,"text":"And this has been invaluable in our approach to try to study these things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"This is my favorite game on airplanes:"},{"time":530000,"text":"where you're in an airplane and you look out the window,"},{"time":532000,"text":"you see the horizon."},{"time":533000,"text":"I always turn my head on the side,"},{"time":535000,"text":"and that simple change makes me go from"},{"time":538000,"text":"seeing this planet as home,"},{"time":540000,"text":"to seeing it as a planet."},{"time":542000,"text":"It's a very simple trick, and I never fail to do it"},{"time":544000,"text":"when I'm sitting in a window seat."},{"time":546000,"text":"Well, this is what we apply to our work."},{"time":548000,"text":"This shows one of the most extreme caves that we work in."},{"time":551000,"text":"This is Cueva de Villa Luz in Tabasco, in Mexico,"},{"time":555000,"text":"and this cave is saturated with sulfuric acid."},{"time":558000,"text":"There is tremendous amounts of hydrogen sulfide"},{"time":560000,"text":"coming into this cave from volcanic sources"},{"time":563000,"text":"and from the breakdown of evaporite --"},{"time":565000,"text":"minerals below the carbonates in which this cave is formed --"},{"time":569000,"text":"and it is a completely hostile environment for us."},{"time":571000,"text":"We have to go in with protective suits and breathing gear,"},{"time":575000,"text":"and 30 parts per million of H2S will kill you."},{"time":580000,"text":"This is regularly several hundred parts per million."},{"time":582000,"text":"So, it's a very hazardous environment,"},{"time":584000,"text":"with CO as well, and many other gases."},{"time":586000,"text":"These extreme physical and chemical parameters"},{"time":589000,"text":"make the biology that grows in these places very special."},{"time":593000,"text":"Because contrary to what you might think, this is not devoid of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":596000,"text":"This is one of the richest caves"},{"time":598000,"text":"that we have found on the planet, anywhere."},{"time":600000,"text":"It's bursting with life."},{"time":602000,"text":"The extremes on Earth are interesting in their own right,"},{"time":604000,"text":"but one of the reasons that we're interested in them"},{"time":606000,"text":"is because they represent, really,"},{"time":608000,"text":"the average conditions that we may expect on other planets."},{"time":611000,"text":"So, this is part of the ability that we have,"},{"time":613000,"text":"to try to stretch our imagination,"},{"time":615000,"text":"in terms of what we may find in the future."},{"time":618000,"text":"There's so much life in this cave,"},{"time":620000,"text":"and I can't even begin"},{"time":622000,"text":"to scratch the surface of it with you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":624000,"text":"But one of the most famous objects out of this"},{"time":626000,"text":"are what we call Snottites, for obvious reasons."},{"time":629000,"text":"This stuff looks like what comes out of your two-year-old's nose when he has a cold."},{"time":633000,"text":"And this is produced by bacteria who are actually"},{"time":636000,"text":"making more sulfuric acid,"},{"time":638000,"text":"and living at pHs right around zero."},{"time":641000,"text":"And so, this stuff is like battery acid."},{"time":643000,"text":"And yet, everything in this cave has adapted to it."},{"time":646000,"text":"In fact, there's so much energy available"},{"time":648000,"text":"for biology in this cave,"},{"time":650000,"text":"that there's actually a huge number of cavefish."},{"time":652000,"text":"And the local Zoque Indians"},{"time":654000,"text":"harvest this twice a year,"},{"time":656000,"text":"as part of their Easter week celebration and Holy Week celebration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":658000,"text":"This is very unusual for caves."},{"time":660000,"text":"In some of the other amazing caves that we work in --"},{"time":663000,"text":"this is in Lechuguilla cave in New Mexico near Carlsbad,"},{"time":667000,"text":"and this is one of the most famous caves in the world."},{"time":670000,"text":"It's 115 miles of mapped passage,"},{"time":672000,"text":"it's pristine, it has no natural opening"},{"time":675000,"text":"and it's a gigantic biological,"},{"time":677000,"text":"geo-microbiological laboratory."},{"time":680000,"text":"In this cave, great areas are covered by"},{"time":683000,"text":"this reddish material that you see here,"},{"time":685000,"text":"and also these enormous crystals"},{"time":687000,"text":"of selenite that you can see dangling down."},{"time":689000,"text":"This stuff is produced biologically."},{"time":692000,"text":"This is the breakdown product of the bedrock,"},{"time":695000,"text":"that organisms are busy munching their way through."},{"time":698000,"text":"They take iron and manganese minerals"},{"time":701000,"text":"within the bedrock and they oxidize them."},{"time":703000,"text":"And every time they do that, they get a tiny little packet of energy."},{"time":707000,"text":"And that tiny little packet of energy is what they use, then,"},{"time":710000,"text":"to run their life processes."},{"time":712000,"text":"Interestingly enough, they also do this"},{"time":714000,"text":"with uranium and chromium, and various other toxic metals."}]},{"cues":[{"time":717000,"text":"And so, the obvious avenue"},{"time":720000,"text":"for bio-remediation"},{"time":722000,"text":"comes from organisms like this."},{"time":724000,"text":"These organisms we now bring into the lab,"},{"time":726000,"text":"and you can see some of them growing on Petri plates,"},{"time":728000,"text":"and get them to reproduce the precise biominerals"},{"time":731000,"text":"that we find on the walls of these caves."},{"time":733000,"text":"So, these are signals that they leave in the rock record."},{"time":736000,"text":"Well, even in basalt surfaces in lava-tube caves,"},{"time":739000,"text":"which are a by-product of volcanic activity,"},{"time":741000,"text":"we find these walls totally covered,"},{"time":743000,"text":"in many cases,"},{"time":745000,"text":"by these beautiful, glistening silver walls,"},{"time":747000,"text":"or shiny pink or shiny red or shiny gold."},{"time":750000,"text":"And these are mineral deposits"},{"time":752000,"text":"that are also made by bacteria."},{"time":754000,"text":"And you can see in these central images here,"},{"time":756000,"text":"scanning electron micrographs of some of these guys --"},{"time":759000,"text":"these are gardens of these bacteria."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761000,"text":"One of the interesting things about these particular guys"},{"time":764000,"text":"is that they're in the actinomycete"},{"time":766000,"text":"and streptomycete groups of the bacteria,"},{"time":768000,"text":"which is where we get most of our antibiotics."},{"time":771000,"text":"The sub-surface of Earth"},{"time":773000,"text":"contains a vast biodiversity."},{"time":775000,"text":"And these organisms,"},{"time":777000,"text":"because they're very separate from the surface,"},{"time":779000,"text":"make a vast array of novel compounds."},{"time":783000,"text":"And so, the potential for exploiting this"},{"time":785000,"text":"for pharmaceutical and industrial chemical uses"},{"time":788000,"text":"is completely untapped,"},{"time":790000,"text":"but probably exceeds most of the rest"},{"time":792000,"text":"of the biodiversity of the planet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":794000,"text":"So, lava-tube caves--"},{"time":796000,"text":"I've just told you about organisms that live here on this planet."},{"time":799000,"text":"We know that on Mars and the Moon"},{"time":801000,"text":"there are tons of these structures."},{"time":803000,"text":"We can see them."},{"time":804000,"text":"On the left you can see a lava tube forming"},{"time":806000,"text":"at a recent eruption -- Mount Etna in Sicily --"},{"time":809000,"text":"and this is the way these tubes form."},{"time":811000,"text":"And when they hollow out,"},{"time":812000,"text":"then they become habitats for organisms."},{"time":815000,"text":"These are all over the planet Mars,"},{"time":817000,"text":"and we're busy cataloguing them now."},{"time":819000,"text":"And so, there's very interesting cave real estate"},{"time":821000,"text":"on Mars, at least of that type."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824000,"text":"In order to access"},{"time":826000,"text":"these sub-surface environments that we're interested in,"},{"time":829000,"text":"we're very interested in developing the tools to do this."},{"time":832000,"text":"You know, it's not easy to get into these caves."},{"time":834000,"text":"It requires crawling, climbing,"},{"time":836000,"text":"rope-work, technical rope-work"},{"time":839000,"text":"and many other complex human motions"},{"time":843000,"text":"in order to access these."},{"time":845000,"text":"We face the problem of, how can we do this robotically?"},{"time":848000,"text":"Why would we want to do it robotically?"},{"time":850000,"text":"Well, we're going to be sending"},{"time":852000,"text":"robotic missions to Mars"},{"time":854000,"text":"long in advance of human missions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":856000,"text":"And then, secondly, getting back to that earlier point that I made"},{"time":859000,"text":"about the preciousness of any life that we may find"},{"time":863000,"text":"on Mars, we don't want to contaminate it."},{"time":865000,"text":"And one of the best ways to study something without contaminating it"},{"time":868000,"text":"is to have an intermediary."},{"time":870000,"text":"And in this case, we're imagining"},{"time":872000,"text":"intermediary robotic devices"},{"time":874000,"text":"that can actually do some of that"},{"time":876000,"text":"front-end work for us,"},{"time":878000,"text":"to protect any potential life that we find."},{"time":880000,"text":"I'm not going to go through all of these projects now,"},{"time":883000,"text":"but we're involved in about half-a-dozen robotic development projects,"},{"time":886000,"text":"in collaboration with a number of different groups."},{"time":889000,"text":"I want to talk specifically about the"},{"time":891000,"text":"array that you see on the top."}]},{"cues":[{"time":893000,"text":"These are hopping microbot swarms."},{"time":896000,"text":"I'm working on this with the Field and Space Robotics Laboratory"},{"time":898000,"text":"and my friend Steve Dubowsky at MIT,"},{"time":901000,"text":"and we have come up with the idea"},{"time":903000,"text":"of having little, jumping bean-like"},{"time":906000,"text":"robots"},{"time":908000,"text":"that are propelled by artificial muscle,"},{"time":911000,"text":"which is one of the Dubowsky Lab's specialties --"},{"time":914000,"text":"are the EPAMs, or artificial muscles."},{"time":916000,"text":"And these allow them to hop."},{"time":918000,"text":"They behave with"},{"time":920000,"text":"a swarm behavior,"},{"time":922000,"text":"where they relate to each other,"},{"time":924000,"text":"modeled after insect swarm behavior,"},{"time":926000,"text":"and they could be made very numerous."},{"time":929000,"text":"And so, one can send a thousand of them,"},{"time":931000,"text":"as you can see in this upper left-hand picture,"},{"time":934000,"text":"a thousand of them could fit into the payload bay"},{"time":937000,"text":"that was used for one of the current MER Rovers."},{"time":940000,"text":"And these little guys -- you could lose many of them."},{"time":943000,"text":"If you send a thousand of them,"},{"time":945000,"text":"you could probably get rid of 90 percent of them and still have a mission."},{"time":947000,"text":"And so, that allows you the flexibility"},{"time":950000,"text":"to go into very challenging terrain"},{"time":953000,"text":"and actually make your way where you want to go."}]},{"cues":[{"time":955000,"text":"Now, to wrap this up, I want to talk for two seconds"},{"time":958000,"text":"about caves and the human expansion beyond Earth"},{"time":961000,"text":"as a natural outgrowth of the work that we do in caves."},{"time":964000,"text":"It occurred to us a number of years ago"},{"time":966000,"text":"that caves have many properties"},{"time":968000,"text":"that people have used"},{"time":970000,"text":"and other organisms have used as habitat in the past."},{"time":972000,"text":"And perhaps it's time we started to explore those,"},{"time":976000,"text":"in the context of future Mars and the Moon exploration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":979000,"text":"So, we have just finished a NASA Institute for Advanced Concepts Phase II study,"},{"time":984000,"text":"looking at the irreducible set of technologies"},{"time":986000,"text":"that you would need in order to"},{"time":988000,"text":"actually allow people to inhabit lava tubes"},{"time":991000,"text":"on the Moon or Mars."},{"time":993000,"text":"It turns out to be a fairly simple and small list,"},{"time":996000,"text":"and we have gone"},{"time":998000,"text":"in the relatively primitive technology direction."},{"time":1000000,"text":"So, we're talking about things like inflatable liners"},{"time":1003000,"text":"that can conform to the complex topological shape"},{"time":1006000,"text":"on the inside of a cave,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"foamed-in-place airlocks to deal with this complex topology,"},{"time":1012000,"text":"various ways of getting breathing gases"},{"time":1015000,"text":"made from the intrinsic materials of these bodies."},{"time":1018000,"text":"And the future is there for us"},{"time":1020000,"text":"to use these lava-tube caves on Mars."},{"time":1023000,"text":"And right now we're in caves, and we're doing science and recreation,"},{"time":1027000,"text":"but I think in the future we'll be using them"},{"time":1029000,"text":"for habitat and science on these other bodies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1031000,"text":"Now, my view of what the current status"},{"time":1034000,"text":"of potential life on Mars is"},{"time":1036000,"text":"that it's probably been on the planet,"},{"time":1039000,"text":"maybe one in two chances."},{"time":1042000,"text":"The question as to whether"},{"time":1045000,"text":"there is life on Mars that is related to life on Earth"},{"time":1049000,"text":"has now been very muddied,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"because we now know,"},{"time":1052000,"text":"from Mars meteorites that have made it to Earth,"},{"time":1055000,"text":"that there's material that can be exchanged between those two planets."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1059000,"text":"One of the burning questions, of course, is"},{"time":1061000,"text":"if we go there and find life in the sub-surface,"},{"time":1064000,"text":"as I fully expect that we will,"},{"time":1066000,"text":"is that a second genesis of life?"},{"time":1068000,"text":"Did life start here"},{"time":1070000,"text":"and was it transported there?"},{"time":1072000,"text":"Did it start there and get transported here?"},{"time":1075000,"text":"This will be a fascinating puzzle as we go into the next half-century,"},{"time":1079000,"text":"and where I expect that we will"},{"time":1081000,"text":"have more and more Mars missions to answer these questions."},{"time":1084000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}